			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Intellect;<br />
<br />
For the end-game, the Buckaneers are like the Bosalians, you have to start grabbing up a bunch of planets and build military bases on them.  The commerce you derive from the planets will be more than enough to pay for the bases and give you extra PP for ship building (especially since commerce is not affected by waste).  Furthermore, you don't even have to invest in the planets, because you don't care how much they are producing since you are just using them as a base for commerce.  And think of how frustrating it will be for someone to take an ultra-rich with nothing but military bases and the bases start building back up on them?  And you have the advantage that you can take just poors and ultra poors from your victims so that they don't feel mad at losing their Ultra Rich or Rich planets.  Do they really want to come after you to get their P/UP planets back?<br />
<br />
And finally, once you have a solid base of commerce planets, you might be able to live in military mode because commerce is not affected by military mode the way production is.  <br />
<br />
Now, where do you find all of those planets?			   <P align=right></P>
